articles.author: Joseph Ax
articles.description: The dizzying presidential contest between Republican Donald Trump and Democrat Kamala Harris hurtled toward an uncertain finish as millions of Americans headed to the polls to choose between two sharply different visions for the country.
articles.title: Voters head to polls as turbulent campaign concludes

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The Israeli military said, without giving details, that its forces had "eliminated terrorists" in the central Gaza Strip and Jabalia area.
articles.title: Israeli airstrikes kill at least 30 Palestinians in Gaza, medics say

articles.author: Rachel More
articles.description: German police have arrested eight suspected members of a neo-Nazi militant group driven by racist ideology and conspiracy theories who had been training in warfare for the downfall of the modern German state, prosecutors said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Germany arrests suspected members of neo-Nazi group plotting revolt

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Spain has earmarked 10.6 billion euros ($11.55 billion) in loans and grants to help the victims of the flash floods that hit the eastern coast of the country around Valencia last week, Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Spain earmarks 10.6 billion euros in loans, grants to flood victims

articles.author: Kate Abnett, Gloria Dickie, Valerie Volcovici
articles.description: European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen will not attend this year's United Nations climate change summit, known as COP29, a Commission spokesperson told Reuters on Tuesday.
articles.title: EU's von der Leyen to skip COP29 climate summit

articles.author: Ariba Shahid
articles.description: Two Chinese nationals were wounded on Tuesday by a private security guard who opened fire at a garment factory in Pakistan's commercial hub Karachi, the latest in a string of attacks that have spurred Beijing to pressure Islamabad to improve security for its citizens.
articles.title: Pakistan shooting wounds two Chinese nationals

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Equatorial Guinea on Tuesday ordered a crackdown on sex in government offices after private videos leaked on social media appeared to show a senior finance ministry official having sex with several women in various places, including his office.
articles.title: Equatorial Guinea orders crackdown on sex in government offices after videos leaked

articles.author: Praveen Paramasivam
articles.description: With sacred chants, ringing of bells and offerings of flowers and bananas, a Hindu priest in Kamala Harris' ancestral village in southern India conducted prayers on Tuesday for her victory in the U.S. presidential election.
articles.title: In her Indian grandfather's village, residents pray for Kamala Harris win

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Africa and Britain have agreed to boost trade and defence cooperation, the two countries' foreign ministers said after meeting on Tuesday.
articles.title: South Africa and Britain to strengthen trade and defence ties

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An Israeli attack targeted an industrial zone and some residential buildings in the town of Qusayr in Homs province in central Syria on Tuesday, Syrian state TV reported.
articles.title: Israeli attack targets town in Syria's Homs province, state TV reports
